      <h1>How Many Ounces in a Gallon? (Conversion Chart)</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">The quick answer: there are <strong>128 fluid ounces in a US gallon</strong>. Whether you are doubling a recipe, tracking your daily water intake, measuring pool chemicals, or figuring out how much juice to buy for a party, knowing this conversion is essential. But the full picture is more nuanced — the US gallon and the UK imperial gallon are different sizes, and the relationship between gallons, quarts, pints, cups, and ounces follows a clean doubling pattern that is easy to memorize once you see it. This guide covers every conversion you need, explains the US vs. imperial differences, and provides practical tables you can bookmark for the kitchen, the garage, or anywhere else you measure liquids.</p>
    </header>

