    <h2>The Quick Answer: 128 Fluid Ounces</h2>
    <p>One US gallon equals exactly 128 US fluid ounces. This is not an approximation — it is a defined relationship in the US customary measurement system. The conversion chain works like this: 1 gallon = 4 quarts, 1 quart = 2 pints, 1 pint = 2 cups, and 1 cup = 8 fluid ounces. Multiply those together: 4 x 2 x 2 x 8 = 128 fluid ounces per gallon.</p>
    <p>This clean doubling relationship makes the US customary system easier to remember than it might first appear. Each step up doubles the previous unit: 8 ounces make a cup, 2 cups make a pint, 2 pints make a quart, and 4 quarts make a gallon. If you can remember "8-2-2-4," you can reconstruct any conversion in the chain.</p>

    <h2>Complete US Liquid Volume Conversion Chart</h2>
    <p>The following table shows the relationships between all common US liquid volume measurements. Bookmark this chart for quick reference when cooking, mixing beverages, or measuring any liquid.</p>
